##Video | on my way to deliver medicine to a new patient, I recharged my battery car in a public restroom

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

Wu You, a 25-year-old middle school teacher, rides a battery-powered cart to deliver medicine to people seeking help online after the city was shut down in Wuhan. So far, he and his friends have delivered medicine and protective gear to more than 600 families seeking help.

Wu Yu goes out every day at 10 o'clock, the battery car can only cycle 30 kilometers once charged, some people live far away, the car's electricity is often not enough, Wu Yu looks for the public toilet to charge the car.

At the beginning, all medicines and protective materials Wu you all free gifts, but there is a scramble, Hoarding Medicine Phenomenon. To target the drugs to patients in need of first aid, Wu negotiated with Sichuan volunteers and decided to sell Oseltamivir, Arbidol, Moxifloxacin and hydroxychloroquine sulfate tablets at a discount to the factory price. The proceeds of the sale are returned to the donor for the continued purchase of medicines. Lianhua Qingwen, masks, alcohol and other protective materials, still free gift.

Recently, someone reported Wu you for illegal sale of drugs and making profits. In cooperation with the investigation, Wu Younan due to cerebral hemorrhage coma, was sent to the hospital.

"The idea was to get the disease over with so that she could get to the hospital early, not get Alzheimer's and not forget about me. "

Here is the full video of Wu you, the medicine man.
